Package kdl.prox.util

Class Summary
Assert Utility class that defines static assertion methods.
ImportUtil Defines basic utilities for importing data via Monet's ascii_io module
MonetUtil Defines static Monet utilities.
PopulateDB Defines the populateDB() static method to aid easily setting up databases The only possibly surprising features are: - comments: start a line with "#" in column zero - OID ranges: Generally, when an OID is expected the program accepts ranges in the form of [START_OID-END_OID] - OID sets: Similarly, you can specify individual OIDs in the form of [OID1,OID2,...]

Example contents for the file:

attributes { O CORE_ATTR_NAME str { [20,21] + } L CONT_LINK_ATTR_NAME flt { # comment 1 10.0 10 11.0 [4,6] 12.0 8 14.0 } }

containers { # comment TEST_CONTAINER { attributes { SUBG_ATTR_NAME dbl { [1,2,4] 1.0 3 2.0 } } subgraph 0 { O 20 CORE_NAME L [1,2] LINK_NAME } subgraph 1 { O [4-5] OBJ_NAME L [3-4] LINK_NAME } } }

links { 0 1 2 5 6 6 # comment }

objects { # here's a comment - '#' must start in column zero [1-3] 5 [11,13] [15-15] [22-21] }

Other samples of the format of this file can be found in test/kdl.prox.util
